  "category": "Strategy & Concepts",
  "sub_category": "General Strategy",
  "description": "A fundamental and ubiquitous scoring technique in basketball where a player jumps straight up and releases the ball near the apex of their jump. While not a team playbook tactic, the jump shot is the foundational atomic action that makes all modern spacing, motion offenses, and small-ball strategies mathematically and spatially viable. It forces defenders to close out and play tight defense on the perimeter, thereby creating driving lanes and offensive gravity.",
